g301.definition: [Ἀμώς] of Hebrew origin ({{h531}}); Amos, an Israelite

g302.definition: [ἄν] a primary particle, denoting a supposition, wish, possibility or uncertainty Usually unexpressed except by the subjunctive or potential mood. Also contracted for {{g1437}}.

g303.definition: [ἀνά] a primary preposition and adverb; properly, up; but (by extension) used (distributively) severally, or (locally) at (etc.) In compounds (as a prefix) it often means (by implication) repetition, intensity, reversal, etc.

g305.definition: [ἀναβαίνω] from {{g303}} and the base of {{g939}}; to go up (literally or figuratively)

g306.definition: [ἀναβάλλομαι] middle voice from {{g303}} and {{g906}}; to put off (for oneself)

g307.definition: [ἀναβιβάζω] from {{g303}} and a derivative of the base of {{g939}}; to cause to go up, i.e. haul (a net)

g308.definition: [ἀναβλέπω] from {{g303}} and {{g991}}; to look up; by implication, to recover sight

g312.definition: [ἀναγγέλλω] from {{g303}} and the base of {{g32}}; to announce (in detail)

g313.definition: [ἀναγεννάω] from {{g303}} and {{g1080}}; to beget or (by extension) bear (again)

g314.definition: [ἀναγινώσκω] from {{g303}} and {{g1097}}; to know again, i.e. (by extension) to read

g316.definition: [ἀναγκαῖος] from {{g318}}; necessary; by implication, close (of kin)

g317.definition: [ἀναγκαστῶς] adverb from a derivative of {{g315}}; compulsorily

g318.definition: [ἀνάγκη] from {{g303}} and the base of {{g43}}; constraint (literally or figuratively); by implication, distress

g319.definition: [ἀναγνωρίζομαι] middle voice from {{g303}} and {{g1107}}; to make (oneself) known

g321.definition: [ἀνάγω] from {{g303}} and {{g71}}; to lead up; by extension to bring out; specially, to sail away

g322.definition: [ἀναδείκνυμι] from {{g303}} and {{g1166}}; to exhibit, i.e. (by implication) to indicate, appoint

g324.definition: [ἀναδέχομαι] from {{g303}} and {{g1209}}; to entertain (as a guest)

g326.definition: [ἀναζάω] from {{g303}} and {{g2198}}; to recover life (literally or figuratively)

g329.definition: [ἀναζωπυρέω] from {{g303}} and a compound of the base of {{g2226}} and {{g4442}}; to re-enkindle

g330.definition: [ἀναθάλλω] from {{g303}} and θάλλω (to flourish); to revive

g331.definition: [ἀνάθεμα] from {{g394}}; a (religious) ban or (concretely) excommunicated (thing or person)

g332.definition: [ἀναθεματίζω] from {{g331}}; to declare or vow under penalty of execration

g333.definition: [ἀναθεωρέω] from {{g303}} and {{g2334}}; to look again (i.e. attentively) at (literally or figuratively)

g334.definition: [ἀνάθημα] from {{g394}} (like {{g331}}, but in a good sense); a votive offering

g335.definition: [ἀναίδεια] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle (compare {{g427}})) and {{g127}}; impudence, i.e. (by implication) importunity

g337.definition: [ἀναιρέω] from {{g303}} and (the active of) {{g138}}; to take up, i.e. adopt; by implication, to take away (violently), i.e. abolish, murder

g338.definition: [ἀναίτιος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g159}} (in the sense of {{g156}}); innocent

g339.definition: [ἀνακαθίζω] from {{g303}} and {{g2523}}; properly, to set up, i.e. (reflexively) to sit up

g340.definition: [ἀνακαινίζω] from {{g303}} and a derivative of {{g2537}}; to restore

g341.definition: [ἀνακαινόω] from {{g303}} and a derivative of {{g2537}}; to renovate

g343.definition: [ἀνακαλύπτω] from {{g303}} (in the sense of reversal) and {{g2572}}; to unveil

g345.definition: [ἀνακεῖμαι] from {{g303}} and {{g2749}}; to recline (as a corpse or at a meal)

g346.definition: [ἀνακεφαλαίομαι] from {{g303}} and {{g2775}} (in its original sense); to sum up

g348.definition: [ἀνακόπτω] from {{g303}} and {{g2875}}; to beat back, i.e. check

g350.definition: [ἀνακρίνω] from {{g303}} and {{g2919}}; properly, to scrutinize, i.e. (by implication) investigate, interrogate, determine

g352.definition: [ἀνακύπτω] from {{g303}} (in the sense of reversal) and {{g2955}}; to unbend, i.e. rise; figuratively, be elated

g355.definition: [ἀναλίσκω] from {{g303}} and a form of the alternate of {{g138}}; properly, to use up, i.e. destroy

g356.definition: [ἀναλογία] from a compound of {{g303}} and {{g3056}}; proportion

g357.definition: [ἀναλογίζομαι] middle voice from {{g356}}; to estimate, i.e. (figuratively) contemplate

g358.definition: [ἄναλος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g251}}; saltless, i.e. insipid

g360.definition: [ἀναλύω] from {{g303}} and {{g3089}}; to break up, i.e. depart (literally or figuratively)

g361.definition: [ἀναμάρτητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g264}}; sinless

g363.definition: [ἀναμιμνήσκω] from {{g303}} and {{g3403}}; to remind; (reflexively) to recollect

g365.definition: [ἀνανεόω] from {{g303}} and a derivative of {{g3501}}; to renovate, i.e. reform

g366.definition: [ἀνανήφω] from {{g303}} and {{g3525}}; to become sober again, i.e. (figuratively) regain (one's) senses

g367.definition: [Ἀνανίας] of Hebrew origin ({{h2608}}); Ananias, the name of three Israelites

g368.definition: [ἀναντίῤῥητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of {{g473}} and {{g4483}}; indisputable

g370.definition: [ἀνάξιος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g514}}; unfit

g373.definition: [ἀναπαύω] from {{g303}} and {{g3973}}; (reflexively) to repose (literally or figuratively (be exempt), remain); by implication, to refresh

g375.definition: [ἀναπέμπω] from {{g303}} and {{g3992}}; to send up or back

g376.definition: [ἀνάπηρος] from {{g303}} (in the sense of intensity) and πῆρος (maimed); crippled

g377.definition: [ἀναπίπτω] from {{g303}} and {{g4098}}; to fall back, i.e. lie down, lean back

g378.definition: [ἀναπληρόω] from {{g303}} and {{g4137}}; to complete; by implication, to occupy, supply; figuratively, to accomplish (by coincidence ot obedience)

g379.definition: [ἀναπολόγητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g626}}; indefensible

g380.definition: [ἀναπτύσσω] from {{g303}} (in the sense of reversal) and {{g4428}}; to unroll (a scroll or volume)

g382.definition: [ἀναρίθμητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g705}}; unnumbered, i.e. without number

g384.definition: [ἀνασκευάζω] from {{g303}} (in the sense of reversal) and a derivative of {{g4632}}; properly, to pack up (baggage), i.e. (by implication, and figuratively) to upset

g385.definition: [ἀνασπάω] from {{g303}} and {{g4685}}; to take up or extricate

g386.definition: [ἀνάστασις] from {{g450}}; a standing up again, i.e. (literally) a resurrection from death (individual, genitive case or by implication, (its author)), or (figuratively) a (moral) recovery (of spiritual truth)

g387.definition: [ἀναστατόω] from a derivative of {{g450}} (in the sense of removal); properly, to drive out of home, i.e. (by implication) to disturb (literally or figuratively)

g390.definition: [ἀναστρέφω] from {{g303}} and {{g4762}}; to overturn; also to return; by implication, to busy oneself, i.e. remain, live

g392.definition: [ἀνατάσσομαι] from {{g303}} and the middle voice of {{g5021}}; to arrange

g393.definition: [ἀνατέλλω] from {{g303}} and the base of {{g5056}}; to (cause to) arise

g394.definition: [ἀνατίθεμαι] from {{g303}} and the middle voice of {{g5087}}; to set forth (for oneself), i.e propound

g395.definition: [ἀνατολή] from {{g393}}; a rising of light, i.e. dawn (figuratively); by implication, the east (also in plural)

g396.definition: [ἀνατρέπω] from {{g303}} and the base of {{g5157}}; to overturn (figuratively)

g397.definition: [ἀνατρέφω] from {{g303}} and {{g5142}}; to rear (physically or mentally)

g398.definition: [ἀναφαίνω] from {{g303}} and {{g5316}}; to show, i.e. (reflexively) appear, or (passively) to have pointed out

g399.definition: [ἀναφέρω] from {{g303}} and {{g5342}}; to take up (literally or figuratively)
